    "body": "@Tribex `transform: scale(2)` doesn't work because it scales everything and the window stays small, plus the GTK menus are still small, and the developer tools are still tiny. The overall app should be scaled with the Desktop's scaling.\n\n@zcbenz If I change `text-scaling-factor` from 1 to 2, my desktop fonts will be extremely huge. Everything in the background of my screenshot is at x1 font-scale. Gnome already scales the whole desktop x2 for retina, but only electron is not scaled. Does it need to read some other setting other than `text-scaling-factor` perhaps?\n"
  },
